      <title>Sifting the Ashes</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This video examines Marshall Ramsey's artwork "Stephanie Sweeney Recovers Her Grandmother's Cast Iron Skillets." The U.S. Department of Commerce's National Institute of Standards and Technology surveyed 323 residents. Ninety-five had never evacuated before. Only 18.3% had had a household emergency plan prior to the fire and 86.7% eventually evacuated last minute. Bob and Stephanie Sweeney, like so many in Gatlinburg, lost nearly everything. If you had to quickly evacuate what would you bring? (Stephanie Sweeney finds her grandmother's cast iron skillets).</abstract>
